      <prop type="x-chinese-ref">老子 41.1</prop>
      <prop type="x-translation-ref">老子 41.1</prop>
      <tuv xml:lang="zh-Hant">
        <seg>上士聞道，勤而行之；</seg>
      </tuv>
      <tuv xml:lang="en">
        <seg>Scholars of the highest class, when they hear about the Dao, earnestly carry it into practice. Scholars of the middle class, when they have heard about it, seem now to keep it and now to lose it. Scholars of the lowest class, when they have heard about it, laugh greatly at it. If it were not (thus) laughed at, it would not be fit to be the Dao.</seg>
      </tuv>
    </tu>
